title: Tracy Chapman, Luke Combs’ Grammys performance of ‘Fast Car’ gets standing ovation
description: Luke Combs and Tracy Chapman performed a duet of "Fast Car" for the first time at the 2024 Grammy Awards. Combs released his own version of Chapman's song in 2023.

title: Taylor Swift impressed by Grammys joke about her camera time during NFL games
description: Taylor Swift seemed pleased with Grammys host Trevor Noah's joke about the global pop star during his opening monologue. A joke about Swift at the Golden Globes fell flat.

title: Kliff Kingsbury to join Commanders as offensive coordinator in wild turn of events: reports
description: The Washington Commanders are bringing in Kliff Kingsbury as their new offensive coordinator in a wild turn of events after he was reported to be joining the Las Vegas Raiders.

title: Florida man garners millions of TikTok followers for posting clever home repair hacks: 'A complete accident'
description: TikTok user jmg8tor has garnered nearly 50 million likes on the social media app for sharing his home repair tips. The Florida resident has nearly 3 million followers.

title: Jim Harbaugh expected to reunite with Greg Roman on Chargers coaching staff: report
description: Jim Harbaugh is expected to reunite with former Baltimore Ravens offensive coordinator Greg Roman, who previously served under him at Stanford and with the San Francisco 49ers.

title: Ocean exploration company's possible proof of Amelia Earhart's wrecked plane nearly vanished: report
description: An ocean exploration that believes it found the wreckage of Amelia Earhart's airplane about 16,000 feet below the surface of the Pacific Ocean nearly lost the images.

title: Saudi Arabia pushes for US defense pact as 2024 presidential election looms
description: Saudi Arabia is seeking to secure a defense pact with the United States ahead of the 2024 presidential election, signaling that it will relax its demands for Palestinian statehood.

title: Paris Jackson's daring Grammy look hides 80+ tattoos: 'I like switching things up'
description: Paris Jackson, daughter of the late Michael Jackson, stepped out on the Grammy red carpet with her tattoos covered by makeup in a surprise look for the young star.

title: Iran issues warning to US about possible attacks on 2 cargo ships suspected of spy activities
description: Iran issued a warning to the U.S. over possibly conducting actions against cargo ships in the Middle East suspected of operating as spy ships.

title: MetLife Stadium chosen to host 2026 World Cup Final
description: FIFA announced Sunday that Metlife Stadium in East Rutherford, New Jersey, has been chosen to host the 2026 World Cup Final; other locations in the U.S. chosen for earlier matches.

title: Florida man arrested after crossing crime scene tape at plane crash site, claimed to be medical staff
description: A 66-year-old Florida man was arrested after trying to sneak past the police crime scene tape at the scene of a fatal plane crash in Clearwater, according to officials.

title: ABC host abruptly ends interview with JD Vance over Supreme Court remarks: 'No, no George'
description: Sen. JD Vance, R-Ohio, spars with ABC News' George Stephanopoulos in interview about the legitimacy of the Supreme Court's rulings.
